entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An AI operating system that enables complex agentic behaviors and facilitates decentralized autonomous organizations (DAOs). It aims to provide a platform for AI agents to perform various tasks and interact within a structured environment.

entities.name: Shaw
entities.description: An individual whose X (formerly Twitter) account was reportedly banned, sparking discussion about potential reasons such as API scraping.

entities.name: DAO
entities.description: Decentralized Autonomous Organization. A blockchain-based organizational structure that operates via smart contracts and community governance, allowing for decentralized decision-making and management of resources.

entities.name: PGLITE
entities.description: A lightweight, serverless SQL database that can be embedded within applications, known for its ease of use and integration capabilities.

entities.name: Twitter Plugin
entities.description: A plugin designed to interact with Twitter (now X) functionalities, likely for posting, fetching data, or managing accounts within an application or platform.

entities.name: RAG
entities.description: Retrieval-Augmented Generation. A technique in AI that combines information retrieval with natural language generation to produce more informed and contextually relevant responses.

entities.name: Bun
entities.description: A fast JavaScript runtime, bundler, and package manager. Logo is a white bun/dumpling on black.

entities.name: pnpm
entities.description: A fast, disk-space-efficient package manager for Node.js. It uses a content-addressable store and hard links to significantly reduce disk usage and speed up installations.

entities.name: bats-assert
entities.description: A package providing assertion utilities for use with the Bats (Bash Automated Testing System) framework, enabling developers to write tests for shell scripts.

entities.name: MEV
entities.description: Maximal Extractable Value (formerly Miner Extractable Value). Refers to the profit that can be made by including, excluding, or changing the order of transactions within a block on a blockchain.

entities.name: L2s
entities.description: Layer 2 scaling solutions for blockchains. These are secondary frameworks or protocols built on top of a robust base layer (Layer 1) to improve transaction speed and reduce costs.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control using Git. It provides tools for software development, collaboration, and code hosting, featuring repositories, pull requests, and issue tracking.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A communication platform designed for communities to chat, voice call, and video call. Popular among gamers and increasingly used for online communities and project discussions.

entities.name: Postgres
entities.description: An open-source object-relational database system known for its reliability, feature robustness, and performance. It is widely used for applications requiring a powerful and scalable database.

entities.name: iOS
entities.description: A mobile operating system created and developed by Apple Inc. exclusively for its hardware, including the iPhone and iPad. It powers a vast ecosystem of mobile applications.

entities.name: X
entities.description: A microblogging and social networking service formerly known as Twitter. Users post and interact with messages known as 'posts'.
